data.description: This home is in a small neighborhood with large lots and no overbearing HOA. The home is in good condition and was built in 2014. As an added benefit, there are solar panels to help reduce energy costs. The utility bill averages around $75/mo but has been as low as $8, and the solar payments are $95/mo. The buyer can finance them into the mortgage or take over payments. There are 4 bedrooms upstairs, 2.1 bathrooms, a living room, an eat-in kitchen, a sunroom, and a sunroom. There are engineered hardwoods, carpet, and vinyl floors. All the bedrooms are a good size. The primary bedroom has a walk-in closet, garden tub and shower, and double vanities. The backyard has a wooden privacy fence, and the yard extends well past the fence line. The location is in a small town, but still not far from I-26, Fort Jackson, downtown Columbia, or Orangeburg. Swansea HS is very close to the neighborhood.
